BIGMART SALES PREDICTION¶

problem statement¶

The data scientists at BigMart have collected 2013 sales data for 1559 products across 10 stores in different cities. Also, certain attributes of each product and store have been defined. The aim is to build a predictive model and find out the sales of each product at a particular store.

Using this model, BigMart will try to understand the properties of products and stores which play a key role in increasing sales

Hyposthesis¶

"Factors such as store location, product type, visibility, promotions, and historical sales data have a significant impact on the sales of various products across different BigMart stores. By analyzing these variables using machine learning techniques, we can develop an accurate model for predicting future sales, enabling BigMart to optimize their operations and increase their revenue."

Summary¶

The error of the model is very high, also the score is too low, both metrics can be improved.either, improving the data or star playing with some hyperparameters to improve the model.Based on the above results RandomForestRegressor gave good accuracy when compared to other model.
